## Cross-page audit

The final review must verify:

- terminology remains distinct for module, package, binding, AST, TIR, HIR,
  access, borrowing, ownership and allocation
- owners remain consistent from Stage 0 through output writing
- accepted, current, queued and deferred status labels remain accurate
- Priya, the file names and the final fragment never change
- each page consumes the previous checkpoint and produces the next one
- each page has three to five visual briefs with alt text, caption, question
  and simplification status
- side examples return to the greeting project
- diagnostics, memory, target and output topics do not duplicate another page

